    "This may result from the factor that the regularization term could slow down the process of learning to be harmless and helpful.",
    "Besides, this finding also suggests that the objectives of being harmless and helpful are actually different.",
    "(3) Overall, FedAvgM [44] performs the best under FedVA for harmlessness and helpfulness.",
    "Discussions and Future DirectionsPreviously, we have shown the promising results achieved by training LLMs via FL (FedLLM), including federated instruction tuning, federated value alignment and their integration with representative FL algorithms.",
